The paper deals with the problem of optimal packet scheduling in an energy harvesting wireless communication system, which involves information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and control systems (cs.SY). The problem is also related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) as the authors analyze the competitive ratio of online algorithms. Finally, the paper uses mathematical optimization techniques to derive bounds on the competitive ratio, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
